question.title: Not able to input date using sendKeys in Selenium WebDriver

node.contents: A direct solution would be something like @Arran said. You should simulate the user selecting a date. I don't know of other workarounds.

astNode.text: A direct solution would be something like @Arran said. You should simulate the user selecting a date. I don't know of other workarounds.

node.contents: I came across this blog [http://blog.reallysimplethoughts.com/2012/07/19/new-selenese-command-sendkeys/] This says that "sendKeys simulates a real user typing every character in the specified string; it is also bound by the limitations of a real user, like not being able to type into a invisible or read only elements." So, it seems typing into the date field is not possible for my app. Can anyone please suggest any other workarounds for selecting the date from calendar?

node.contents: I had the same issue, but with Telerik's RadCalendar (.NET), for me the issue was worked around by physically using the calendar to simulate clicking a date.

node.contents: Since mine is data driven framework, simulating click on a date(dynamic) will be a bit difficult. I got this working by using JavascriptExecutor like: `((JavascriptExecutor)driver).executeScript("arguments[0].value=arguments[1]", driver.findElement(By.id(stringc3)), stringc4);` where stringc3 is the locator id of the date field and stringc4 is the date like "01-01-2012"

node.contents: If You are using a jQuery date picker object, the field should be read-only and date have to be selected from calendar object. In that case You can use 'Select' class methods of Selenium Web Driver to choose a date.

astNode.text: If You are using a jQuery date picker object, the field should be read-only and date have to be selected from calendar object. In that case You can use 'Select' class methods of Selenium Web Driver to choose a date.

elements.contents: Select date = new Select(driver.findElement(By.linkText("the date want to select"))); date.click();

units.rawText: Select date = new Select(driver.findElement(By.linkText("the date want to select"))); dateclick();

node.contents: I also faced the same issue.This is what the solution I found.This worked fine for me. Just remove the read only attribute of the input field and then do just as other input fields.

astNode.text: I also faced the same issue.This is what the solution I found.This worked fine for me. Just remove the read only attribute of the input field and then do just as other input fields.

elements.contents: ((JavascriptExecutor)driver).executeScript ("document.getElementById('dateofbirth').removeAttribute('readonly',0);"); WebElement BirthDate= driver.findElement(By.id("dateofbirth")); BirthDate.clear(); BirthDate.sendKeys("20-Aug-1985"); //Enter this date details with valid date format
